segment.source: The Parse Items tab displays the mapping rules that the Sequencer uses to accommodate differences that exist between configurations on the sequencing computer and the App-V Desktop Client.
segment.target: The Parse Items tab displays the mapping rules that the Sequencer uses to accommodate differences that exist between configurations on the sequencing computer and the App-V Desktop Client.

segment.source: This tab contains the following elements.
segment.target: This tab contains the following elements.

segment.source: Displays read-only variable names evaluated by the Application Virtualization Sequencer to determine important operating system locations on the sequencing computer.
segment.target: Displays read-only variable names evaluated by the Application Virtualization Sequencer to determine important operating system locations on the sequencing computer.

segment.source: Displays read-only variable names that the Application Virtualization Sequencer substitutes when encountering variable names in the associated Parse From column, while parsing items in the virtual file system or virtual registry.
segment.target: Displays read-only variable names that the Application Virtualization Sequencer substitutes when encountering variable names in the associated Parse From column, while parsing items in the virtual file system or virtual registry.

segment.source: Displays read-only mapping rules that the Application Virtualization Sequencer applies to parse items in the virtual file system or virtual registry.
segment.target: Displays read-only mapping rules that the Application Virtualization Sequencer applies to parse items in the virtual file system or virtual registry.
